# CyberSIP — Project Context

CyberSIP is a **Cybersecurity Sales Intelligence Platform** — a specialized CRM for cybersecurity sales teams focused on competitor tracking, market intelligence, and contract lifecycle management.

> "Don't just record what happened; predict what should happen next."

## Architecture

Three-tier decoupled architecture: **Browser → Next.js → FastAPI → Prisma → PostgreSQL**

| Layer      | Tech                                               | Port |
|------------|-----------------------------------------------------|------|
| Frontend   | Next.js 16, React 19, TypeScript, shadcn/ui, Tailwind CSS 4, TanStack Query | 3000 |
| Backend    | Python 3.12, FastAPI, Pydantic, prisma-client-py   | 8000 |
| Database   | PostgreSQL 16, Prisma ORM                           | 5432 |
| Infra      | Docker Compose                                      |      |

**Critical rules:**
- The frontend is a **pure UI layer** — it NEVER touches the database directly
- All data flows through FastAPI endpoints — the frontend only calls the backend REST API
- Prisma lives on the **backend only** via `prisma-client-py`
- External services (AI, N8N, enrichment) are always accessed via backend — frontend never calls them directly

## Project Structure

```
cybersip/
├── frontend/          # Next.js 16 App Router
│   ├── app/           # Pages (Command Center, Hunt, Intelligence, Sales Recon, Portfolio, Territories, Vault, Settings)
│   ├── components/    # Shared UI components (shadcn/ui based)
│   ├── hooks/         # TanStack Query hooks (use-companies, etc.)
│   └── lib/           # API client (lib/api.ts), types (lib/types.ts), utilities
├── backend/           # FastAPI Python API
│   ├── app/main.py    # FastAPI app entry
│   ├── app/routers/   # 9 CRUD routers (companies, contacts, engagements, assignments, products, contracts, competitors, territories, teams)
│   ├── app/schemas/   # Pydantic schemas
